CAPE TOWN - Northern Cape police have uncovered drugs worth over R500,000. Officers arrested three suspected drug dealers in Danielskuil on Monday. Police spokesperson Olebogeng Tawana said that they uncovered large batches of dagga, crystal meth and tik. “Cyrstal meth weighing 310 grams to the value of the R77,500 was found on the suspect with R1,600 cash believed to be the proceeds of the sales of the drugs.” #sapsNC #SAPS members arrested three suspects for dealing in drugs during Operation Vhuthu Hawe in Danielskuil.  Drugs with an estimated value of more than R500 000 and cash were confiscated. #DrugsOffTheStreet SWhttps://t.co/3LdK9HCxHa pic.twitter.com/GIMUgboSx1 